Date:  0/0/1898
Source:  Austral English
Author:  MORRIS
Vol / Page:  164
Edition:
Quote:  ~ the desire to obtain gold by digging. The word is more especially applied to the period between 1851 and 1857, the early Australian discovery of gold. The term had been previously applied in a similar way to the Californian excitement in 1848-49. Called also Yellow-fever. [1888]
